&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;outer core&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/important-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Important Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The interior of the earth is divided into three parts namely &lt;strong&gt;Crust, Mantle, and Core.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The core&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;is&amp;nbsp;the innermost layer of the earth.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The radius of the innermost layer(core) is about &lt;strong&gt;3500 km.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The core is made up of&amp;nbsp;material&amp;nbsp;constituted by &lt;strong&gt;nickel and iron.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The temperature and pressure of the central core are very high.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The core is further subdivided into two layers called the &lt;strong&gt;outer core and inner core.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The outer core of the earth is in a liquid state.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The inner core is in solid-state&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The outer core is responsible for the&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;earth&amp;#39;s magnetic field.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;crust&lt;/strong&gt; is the outermost&amp;nbsp;of the earth.

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It is brittle in nature.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;it the thinnest layer of Earth.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The thickness of the crust varies under the oceanic and continental areas.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;The mantle&lt;/b&gt; is the second layer in the interior of the earth.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The mantle extends from Moho&amp;rsquo;s discontinuity to a depth of 2,900 km.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The upper portion of the mantle is called the asthenosphere.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;//storage.googleapis.com/tb-img/production/22/05/5fce010148d677ef4308b9e3_16539950484611.png&quot; style=&quot;height: 348px; width: 350px;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;Option 1 &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/in_news.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;In News&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;list-style-type: disc;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The film Haq, inspired by the Shah Bano case, has renewed public interest in the historic Supreme Court judgment that sparked national debate on secularism, minority rights, and gender justice in India.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;list-style-type: disc;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The &lt;em&gt;Shah Bano case (1985)&lt;/em&gt; involved a 62-year-old Muslim woman from Indore who sought maintenance from her husband under Section 125 of the Code of Criminal Procedure (CrPC), 1973, which provides maintenance to dependents unable to support themselves. &lt;strong&gt;Hence, Option A is correct. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The Supreme Court ruled that Muslim women are entitled to maintenance from their former husbands, like women of any other religion, under secular law.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The verdict led to political controversy and the enactment of the Muslim Women (Protection of Rights on Divorce) Act, 1986, which sought to nullify the judgment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;list-style-type: disc;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The 1986 Act was later reviewed by the Supreme Court in 2001, and again in 2024, where the Court clarified that the Act does not bar divorced Muslim women from seeking maintenance under Section 125 CrPC.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The Shah Bano verdict remains a landmark in discussions about gender justice and the Uniform Civil Code.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Prataprao Jadhav.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/in_news.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;In News&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Ministry of Ayush will host the Departmental Summit on &lt;u&gt;National Ayush Mission (NAM)&lt;/u&gt; and &lt;u&gt;Capacity Building in States&lt;/u&gt; on &lt;u&gt;3&amp;ndash;4 September&lt;/u&gt; at &lt;u&gt;AIIA, New Delhi&lt;/u&gt;, to be chaired by &lt;u&gt;Minister of State Prataprao Jadhav&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Prataprao Jadhav&lt;/u&gt;, Minister of State, will chair the two-day national summit.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;As chair, he will lead deliberations to strengthen &lt;u&gt;NAM&lt;/u&gt; and support &lt;u&gt;state capacity building&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;He will steer collaboration among &lt;u&gt;States and UTs&lt;/u&gt; to promote &lt;u&gt;holistic healthcare&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Discussions chaired by him will draw on &lt;u&gt;NITI Aayog&amp;rsquo;s six thematic sub-groups&lt;/u&gt; covering financial management, QA of Ayush medicine, IT and more.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;National Ayush Mission (NAM)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The summit aims to &lt;u&gt;strengthen NAM&lt;/u&gt; and its implementation across States/UTs.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Aligned with promoting &lt;u&gt;holistic healthcare&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Capacity Building in States&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Focus on improving state-level systems, workforce readiness, and implementation support.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Envisions better coordination between States and UTs.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;NITI Aayog Thematic Sub-Groups&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Six themes identified to drive discussions, including &lt;u&gt;financial management&lt;/u&gt;, &lt;u&gt;quality assurance of Ayush medicine&lt;/u&gt;, and &lt;u&gt;IT&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Event Details&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;Dates&lt;/u&gt;: 3&amp;ndash;4 September; &lt;u&gt;Venue&lt;/u&gt;: &lt;u&gt;AIIA, New Delhi&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Objective: Strengthen NAM, enhance capacity, and foster inter-state collaboration.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;option 2&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;India&amp;#39;s First E-Voter:&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Bibha Kumari, from Pakridayal, East Champaran, Bihar, became India&amp;#39;s first e-voter.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;She cast the inaugural mobile-based electronic vote during the municipal bypolls in June 2025.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Bihar&amp;#39;s Initiative:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Bihar became the first state in India to implement a mobile voting system.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The system was introduced to enable eligible voters&amp;mdash;such as senior citizens, persons with disabilities, pregnant women, and migrant workers&amp;mdash;to vote remotely.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;E-SECBHR App:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The mobile voting system was facilitated through the E-SECBHR app.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The app allowed for secure voting by using advanced technologies like blockchain encryption, facial recognition, voter ID verification, and device restrictions.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Voter Participation:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;70.20% of registered voters utilized the mobile e-voting system.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;This turnout was notably higher than the 54.6% turnout at traditional polling booths.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Security Features:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The system ensured secure and verifiable voting through:
		&lt;ul&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;Blockchain encryption&lt;/li&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;Facial recognition&lt;/li&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;Voter ID verification&lt;/li&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;Device restrictions&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ul&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The incorrect option is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;As of August 2025, 50 semiconductor manufacturing and packaging projects have been approved in the country.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/in_news.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;In News&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Finance Minister Nirmala Sitharaman announced the launch of India Semiconductor Mission (ISM) 2.0 in the Union Budget 2026 presented on February 1, 2026.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); &quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;India Semiconductor Mission (ISM) 2.0:&lt;/strong&gt; The mission aims to produce equipment and materials, develop &lt;strong&gt;full-stack Indian IP&lt;/strong&gt; (Intellectual Property), and strengthen supply chains. It builds on the capabilities of ISM 1.0.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); &quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Project Status:&lt;/strong&gt; As of August 2025, &lt;strong&gt;10 semiconductor manufacturing and packaging projects&lt;/strong&gt; (not 50) have been approved in the country with a cumulative investment of around &lt;strong&gt;₹1.6 lakh crore&lt;/strong&gt; in six States.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); &quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Research &amp;amp; Workforce:&lt;/strong&gt; The new mission will focus on &lt;strong&gt;industry-led research&lt;/strong&gt; and training centres to develop technology and a skilled workforce.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); &quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Electronics Boost:&lt;/strong&gt; The outlay for the Electronics Components Manufacturing Scheme is proposed to be increased to &lt;strong&gt;₹40,000 crore&lt;/strong&gt; to capitalise on the momentum.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); &quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Budget Facts 2026&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Date &amp;amp; Day:&lt;/strong&gt; Presented on February 1, 2026, which was a &lt;strong&gt;Sunday&lt;/strong&gt; (a historic first).&lt;/li&gt;
