&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/in_news.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle; font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;In News&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Adani Group is constructing a 12.9 km ropeway from Sonprayag to Kedarnath under the National Ropeways Development Programme&amp;mdash;Parvatmala Pariyojana, aiming to cut travel time from 9 hours to just 36 minutes.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle; font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The ropeway will span 12.9 km, connecting Sonprayag to Kedarnath, reducing travel time from nearly nine hours to 36 minutes.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The ₹4,081 crore project will use Tri-cable Detachable Gondola (3S) technology, ensuring stability and safety in high-altitude terrain.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;It will have a carrying capacity of 1,800 passengers per hour per direction, catering to thousands of Char Dham pilgrims.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Adani Enterprises Ltd received the Letter of Award in September 2025 and will construct the ropeway under the PPP model, operating it for 29 years after a six-year construction period.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle; font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Parvatmala Pariyojana&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Launched by the Government of India to promote ropeway development in hilly and difficult terrains.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Aims to improve connectivity, reduce travel time, and promote tourism in mountainous regions.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Encourages Public-Private Partnership (PPP) for efficient implementation.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Project Details&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Cost: ₹4,081 crore&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Length: 12.9 km&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Technology: 3S (Tri-cable Detachable Gondola)&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Time reduction: 9 hours to 36 minutes&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Capacity: 1,800 passengers/hour/direction&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Regional Impact&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Boosts tourism and employment in Uttarakhand&amp;rsquo;s high-altitude region.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Ensures safer travel for pilgrims, especially the elderly and differently-abled.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Promotes local economic development while maintaining environmental safeguards.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Vaibhav Suryavanshi, Kanishk Chouhan, Henil Patel.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/in_news.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;In News&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Three Indian players were selected in the Team of the Tournament for the ICC Under-19 Men&amp;rsquo;s Cricket World Cup 2026.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Vaibhav Suryavanshi was the leading run-scorer of the tournament with 439 runs.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Kanishk Chouhan played a key role as a consistent top-order batsman.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Henil Patel made significant contributions with the ball during crucial matches.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The Team of the Tournament represents the best performers across all participating teams.&lt;/li&gt;
